import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming the dataframe is loaded into 'df'
# Analysis for Age and Cancer Types

# Grouping by age and cancer site
age_cancer_group = data.groupby(['Age recode with <1 year olds', 'Site recode ICD-O-3/WHO 2008']).size().unstack()

# Plotting the results
age_cancer_group.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title('Cancer Types Across Different Age Groups')
plt.xlabel('Age Group')
plt.ylabel('Number of Cases')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1,1), ncol=2)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Assuming your DataFrame is named df
# Calculate the count of cases for each cancer type and gender
cancer_counts = data.groupby(['Sex', 'Site recode ICD-O-3/WHO 2008']).size().reset_index(name='counts')

# Get the top 5 cancer types for each gender
top_cancer_types = (cancer_counts.groupby('Sex')
                    .apply(lambda x: x.nlargest(5, 'counts'))
                    .reset_index(drop=True))

# Get a list of these top cancer types
top_cancer_types_list = top_cancer_types['Site recode ICD-O-3/WHO 2008'].unique()

# Filter the original df to include only the top cancer types
filtered_cancer_counts = cancer_counts[cancer_counts['Site recode ICD-O-3/WHO 2008'].isin(top_cancer_types_list[:5])]

# Pivot the data
cancer_counts_pivot = filtered_cancer_counts.pivot(index='Site recode ICD-O-3/WHO 2008', columns='Sex', values='counts')

# Plotting
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

# Plot a grouped bar chart
cancer_counts_pivot.plot(kind='bar', ax=ax)

# Set plot title and labels
ax.set_title('Gender Differences in Top 5 Cancer Types')
ax.set_xlabel('Cancer Type')
ax.set_ylabel('Count of Cases')

# Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')

# Show legend
ax.legend(title='Sex')

# Adjust layout to make room for x-axis labels
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()
